抜群
ばつぐん【抜群】 ﾛｰﾏ(batsugun)
top drawer; high quality; excellence.
〜の top-drawer; outstanding; conspicuous; distinguished; exceptional 《results》.
▲人気抜群の選手　an outstandingly popular player
・歌唱力抜群の歌手　a singer with an ⌐outstandingly [exceptionally] powerful voice
・汚れ落ち抜群の洗剤　a detergent which is exceptionally effective at getting out the dirt
・抜群の能力を持っている　have ⌐outstanding [exceptional] abilities; be ⌐outstanding [exceptional] 《at doing, in one's abilities》
・抜群の強さを発揮する　display outstanding powers; be far stronger than anyone else; be tremendous
・抜群の成績で卒業する　graduate from 《school》 with ⌐distinction [outstanding results]
・抜群の功績があったとして彼は表彰された.　He received an award for his outstanding achievements.
▲…にかけては抜群である　be ⌐outstanding [preeminent] for…; excel 《others》 in….
▲その試合における彼の働きは抜群であった.　His role in the game was quite outstanding. ｜ He made a distinguished contribution to the game.
抜群に　oustandingly; exceptionally; conspicuously; singularly 《gifted》; 《文》 preeminently.
▲彼は抜群に冗談がうまいので, クラスの人気者だ.　He is exceptionally good at jokes so he is very popular in the class. ｜ His tremendous sense of humor makes him very popular in the class.
・足の速い動物はいろいろいるが, その中でもチーターは抜群に速い.　A lot of animals are fast runners, but the cheetah is ⌐way ahead of the rest [preeminent in this respect].
・握りを変えただけで, ボールが抜群に飛ぶようになった.　I just changed my grip slightly and the ball really flew.
抜群になる　become ⌐outstanding [exceptional]; get (way) ahead; (come to) ⌐stand [stick] out.
▲毎日のようにマスコミに取り上げられたのでその村は一躍知名度が抜群になった.　Taken up by the media everyday, the village suddenly ⌐found itself famous [shot to prominence].
